citeinfo.title: WATER BODY IDENTIFICATION NUMBERS (WBID - RUN 55) FOR THE STATE OF FLORIDA - JULY 2018

pubinfo.publish: Florida Department of Environmental Protection, Watershed Assessment Section

descript.abstract: This is a statewide polygon layer in which each polygon has a unique Water Body Identification number (WBID - RUN 55). The assessment units are drainage basins, lakes, lake drainage areas, springs, rivers and streams, segments of rivers and streams, coastal, bay and estuarine waters in Florida. The polygons roughly delineate the drainage basins surrounding the water body assessment units. The WBIDs are used in the Basin Rotation Total Maximum Daily Load (TMDL) program as well as other applications. WBIDs are assigned a FDEP district as part of their attribution. There are multiple instances where a WBID may be assigned to an FDEP district, but physically fall within the boundary of a different district. This is because WBIDs are grouped together into basins called Planning Units and there are instances where a Planning Unit basin will fall across FDEP district boundaries. In these cases, for consistency's sake, all the WBIDs that are in the Planning Unit will be assigned to the same FDEP district. For information on which district the WBID physically falls in, please refer to the FDEP Regulatory Districts layer. This is an update to the FGDL layer WBIDS_DEC17.
descript.purpose: To spatially represent the water feature that is being assessed.

The Watershed Rotation Groups and Schedule (Proposed) coverage was created from the drainage basins coverage (basin-24 (area)). The watershed groups were created by unioning the drainage basins in the basin-24 cover. The watershed groups generally follow the boundaries of the USGS 8-digit HUCS. (Creation of the basin-24 (area) dataset) In Spring of '97, the data was converted from NAD27 to HPGN using the Arc/INFO projection command within Arc/INFO version 7.0.4. One coverage of the entire state, excluding South Florida was digitized using ARC/INFO. The South Florida coverage was digitized by SFWMD from USGS mylars of 7.5' quads dated 1978-1979 by engineers familiar with the landscape using ARC/INFO 6.1.1. The two coverages were joined to form a statewide coverage using the update command, then polygon slivers were eliminated. Check plots were made. The coverage was converted to Albers Conformal Area projection and exported from the VAX VMS system using ARC/INFO. On the DEC/ALPHA UNIX system, the export file was imported and inserted into the (quad) library. Since the original creation of the WBIDS spatial dataset recommended changes to the linework by basin rotation staff and outside professionals have been incorporated on a case by case basis. These changes are documented in the CHANGES column of the dataset. During August of 2003 the ARC coverage was converted into a Geodatabase to facilitate the editing process in ARCGIS. Geodatabase is joined to Access IWR database to get information in specific waterbodies. For more information, contact the Department of Environmental Protection or South Florida Water Management District for copies of data dictionaries. Dataset copied.
